gap by analyzing Elizabeth and her supporters’ use of the Old Testament to provide justification for decisions (or the lack thereof), to offer counsel to the Queen, and to vindicate both female kingship and the royal supremacy. It argues that biblical analogies were a vital component of Elizabethan royal iconography, and that their widespread use demonstrates their potency as a tool for legitimizing and sustaining her power.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBible and politicsxHistoryy16th centuryzEngland. 0aBible and politicszEnglandxHistoryy16th century. 0aDivine right of kings. 0aMonarchyxReligious aspectsxHistoryy16th century. 0aQueenship and power. 7aHISTORY / Europe / Great Britain / Tudor & Elizabethan Era (1485-1603).2bisacsh  aElizabeth I.  aOld Testament.  abiblical analogies.  aearly modern religion.  apolitics and religion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311102374808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishz978311131913108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2023z9783111318189oZDB-23-DEG40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781802700770?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781802700770423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781802700770/original  a978-3-11-102374-8  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131913-1  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS